VACANCY ANNOUNCEMENT
 
 
Risk Education Officer - Amman
 
 
Position: Risk Education Officer
Job Location: Amman
Reporting to: Mine Action Manager
Closing date: 26 March 2017
 
NGO PRESENTATION
 
Handicap International (HI) is an independent and impartial international aid organisation working in situations of poverty and exclusion, conflict and disaster. Working alongside persons with disabilities and other vulnerable groups, our action and testimony are focused on responding to their essential needs, improving their living conditions and promoting respect for their dignity and their fundamental rights.
 
HI is a not-for-profit organisation with no religious or political affiliation. It operates as a federation made up of a network of associations that provide it with human and financial resources, manage its projects and implement its actions and social mission.
 
HI has been present in the Middle East since 1987 through its Development Department. HI started to respond to the Syrian crisis in late 2012 through several hubs in the Middle East, and launched assistance to Syrian refugees in Jordan in 2013.
 
MISSION CONTEXT
 
The Syrian crisis is the greatest humanitarian crisis of the last 20 years. According to the latest UN figures, about 13.5 million people are currently affected by the crisis in Syria, including about 6.5 million IDPs, while over 4 million Syrians have sought refuge in neighbouring countries or in Europe. The current humanitarian response only provides a patchy and partial coverage of the growing humanitarian needs. Five years after the beginning of the crisis, the number of injured persons in Syria keeps rising, with a severe lack of rehabilitative care and psychosocial support. In hard-to-reach areas and/or areas of new displacement, local populations and IDPs are in need of emergency assistance in terms of food, household essential items, and other basic needs.                                                              
 
ACCOUNTABILITIES
 
Based in Amman, the Risk Education Officer will be responsible for the overall implementation of the risk awareness activities, including technical supervision, support and training.
 

Supervision and monitoring of Risk education activities.

 
Activity implementation
 

Assist technically the line manager to ensure the project meets its objectives and maximizes the positive impact of its activities;
Ensure that all Risk Education activities are implemented to a high standard, in line with International Mine Action Standards (IMAS) and HI standard operating procedures (SOPs);
Oversee the implementation of current activities implemented by partners staffs through regular discussions with them for updates and information gathering about any issues faced by the team (linked to equipment/material, facilities, context evolutions, etc.);
Report issues to the line manager and other relevant HI staff depending on the nature of difficulties encountered , and suggest potential improvements;
Contribute to the identification of needs for adaptation of current activities or design of new activities, and report feedback to the Line Manager;
Contribute to the development of training materials as required;
Assist technically the Line Manager to link Risk Education activities with HI other sectors of activities implemented.

 
Monitoring and evaluation 
 

Ensure that the monitoring documents are received on time, providing reminders to partner staff if necessary;
Check the compliance with defined methodologies and proper use of monitoring and data collection tools, requesting clarifications and providing feedback to partners if needed;
Regularly extract specific data through the documents sent by partners’ staff, send it along with analysis of this data to the line manager and other relevant HI staff;
Transfer all the monitoring and follow-up documents to HI Database Officer for data entry and analysis.

 

Technical supervision, support and training 

 

Check compliance with international and organizational standards (framework, tools and procedures) in the implementation of activities;
Through regular discussions with partners’ staff, collect information about any technical issues faced by the teams;
Report on these issues to the Line Manager and provide reminders, recommendations or support to partners in case of any breach to ensure compliance with standards;
Collect and analyze the training needs of the partners’ staff;
Contributes towards meeting those training needs through development/adaptation of training contents and materials in close collaboration with relevant technical staff (HI or other reliable sources);
Deliver these trainings to partner staff with methods, approaches, tools and techniques useful for the project implementation, if needed;
Assess the trainees’ level prior and after any training sessions as to adjust the training content accordingly, and record data on trainees’ improvements.

 
 

Support to the design and implementation of Risk Education tools and processes

 

Contribute to the design/adaptation of current or new project follow-up, monitoring and quality assurance tools related to Risk Education activities, complying with harmonization requirements at regional level;
Help adapt and implement the information management and exchange component of the project, in close collaboration with HI technical and other relevant staff.

 
 

Coordination and Reporting

 

Perform regular meetings with partners and draft minutes of meeting for each of them;
Closely monitor the progress of the implementation and its indicators;
Contribute to monthly situation reports and project management box, project proposals and reports upon request;
Participate in team meetings and other internal coordination mechanisms;
Prepare and update a monthly action plan;
Provide reports / summaries of any trainings given.

 
 

Confidentiality 

 

Respect the confidentiality of all information and data received;
Restrict information sharing only to relevant internal staff and none to external sources;
Respect and promote HI’s policies and report to the line manager any non-respect of these policies amongst the teams or partners;
Address needs and requests in a professional way;
Report any incident or act that causes any harm to beneficiary or to others.

 
 

Other

 
Translation: 
 

Ensure the translation of tools, training materials or project documents necessary to the activities from English to Arabic (and vice versa as needed);
Assist any member of the team in translating when meeting partners or external actors.

 
Lessons learning and capitalization:
 

